					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I thought you were searching for an appropriate word to describe something, not trying to figure out how a particular idea is described on the wiki. I don't think the wiki says &quot;tone&quot;.<br /><br />Here are a few terms the wiki might use, and a description of how they might be components of a &quot;note&quot;:<br /><ul><li><strong>envelope / volume</strong> - controls where a note starts and stops, and how loud it is over time</li><li><strong>period / frequency / pitch</strong> - controls how &quot;high&quot; or &quot;low&quot; the tone of the note is (e.g. &quot;G-3&quot; vs &quot;C-2&quot;)</li><li><strong>duty</strong> - controls the timbre or &quot;texture&quot; of the note (e.g. clarinet vs. oboe)</li></ul></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

